No.
Then what we're saying is

04:20.378 --> 04:21.994
she's a crazy stalker bitch
who pulled that fire alarm

04:21.995 --> 04:23.429
and you should
run screaming.

04:23.431 --> 04:24.380
You know what?

04:24.382 --> 04:25.331
I-I don't think

04:25.333 --> 04:26.799
that we should be so cavalier

04:26.801 --> 04:28.217
with the word "stalker."

04:28.219 --> 04:30.303
Why does that word
bother you so much?

04:30.305 --> 04:31.554
Doesn't bother me.

04:31.556 --> 04:34.307
Wait... do you
have a stalker?

04:35.675 --> 04:36.893
I don't want to talk
about this.

04:36.895 --> 04:37.944
What do you mean?

04:37.946 --> 04:39.278
As your fiancé,
if you have

04:39.280 --> 04:41.314
some psycho stalker out
there, I should know.

04:41.316 --> 04:42.615
It was me.

04:42.617 --> 04:43.983
I was a stalker.

04:43.985 --> 04:45.735
It was back
in Canada.

04:45.737 --> 04:47.236
I liked a guy

04:47.238 --> 04:50.022
and he didn't
like me, and...

04:50.024 --> 04:51.524
well, I got
a little obsessed.

04:51.526 --> 04:54.293
I'd fill up my journals
all about him,

04:54.295 --> 04:56.462
and eventually
there may have been

04:56.464 --> 04:59.532
a teensy-weensy
50-meter restraining order.

04:59.534 --> 05:01.700
50 meters?

05:01.702 --> 05:02.718
That's like...

05:02.720 --> 05:04.720
four years.

05:05.389 --> 05:06.472
Wow.

05:06.474 --> 05:08.558
You must have been
a total nutbag.

05:08.560 --> 05:09.542
I wasn't.

05:09.544 --> 05:10.543
Ted is right,

05:10.545 --> 05:11.677
there is
a fine line.

05:11.679 --> 05:13.596
Anyone can cross it
and get obsessed.

05:13.598 --> 05:15.731
Yeah, if you're
a total nutbag.

05:17.101 --> 05:19.352
Now, uh...
who's the guy?

05:19.354 --> 05:20.770
I'm not telling you
until you admit

05:20.772 --> 05:22.188
that this can happen
to anybody.

05:22.190 --> 05:23.222
I'm not admitting that.

05:23.224 --> 05:24.440
Fine. Forget it.
I'm not telling you.

