06:27.788 --> 06:29.755
<i>Could not</i>

06:29.757 --> 06:32.475
stand the idea

06:32.477 --> 06:34.143
of not meeting me.

06:34.145 --> 06:35.511
Was it a little

06:35.513 --> 06:37.980
over the top to pull
that fire alarm? Perhaps.

06:38.732 --> 06:39.815
But it charmed me.

06:39.817 --> 06:41.901
Hence... Dobler.

06:42.736 --> 06:44.353
Aha! You see?

06:44.355 --> 06:46.022
People don't put fire alarms

06:46.024 --> 06:48.658
out in front lobbies
for just anyone to prank pull.

06:48.660 --> 06:50.109
They put smoke detectors

06:50.111 --> 06:51.527
up on the ceiling.

06:51.529 --> 06:53.245
Hold on.

06:53.247 --> 06:55.448
I'm beginning to think
that you guys didn't come here

06:55.450 --> 06:56.999
to see my new lectern.

06:57.001 --> 06:59.619
Are you implying
Jeanette started a fire?

06:59.621 --> 07:00.703
Dahmer.

07:00.705 --> 07:02.305
Dobler.

07:02.307 --> 07:03.673
She's John Cusack,

07:03.675 --> 07:05.041
I'm Ione Skye,

07:05.043 --> 07:07.326
and there is nothing
weird about that.

07:11.214 --> 07:12.715
Gordie Bellavoh.

07:12.717 --> 07:14.550
Thanks again for
the free donuts, eh?

07:14.552 --> 07:17.169
So, you up here
visiting family?

07:17.171 --> 07:19.355
No. I'm not Canadian.

07:19.357 --> 07:21.307
Not even a quarter Canadian
on my father's side.

07:21.309 --> 07:22.642
Shut up.

07:23.694 --> 07:24.727
We're not talking "aboot" me--

07:24.729 --> 07:27.697
<i>about</i> me. Whoa.

07:27.699 --> 07:29.065
How long did you and Robin date?

07:29.067 --> 07:31.117
Well, it wasn't
really dating.

07:31.119 --> 07:33.285
We'd take a sixer of Labatts
behind the hydro plant

07:33.287 --> 07:36.288
