No. We only went out
a few times,

07:50.838 --> 07:51.804
barely knew each other.

07:51.806 --> 07:53.139
All we talked about

07:53.141 --> 07:54.724
was her relationship
with her mother,

07:54.726 --> 07:56.425
the gnawing feelings
of inadequacy,

07:56.427 --> 07:59.011
all the horrible secrets
on that side of the family.

07:59.013 --> 08:00.879
But heck, you're her fiancé.

08:00.881 --> 08:02.214
You know all that, right?

08:02.216 --> 08:03.882
Yeah.

08:03.884 --> 08:05.050
Robin was

08:05.052 --> 08:07.219
way more into this other guy.

08:07.938 --> 08:10.072
Can't seem to remember his name.

08:10.074 --> 08:11.190
Though sometimes
a powdered jelly

08:11.192 --> 08:12.891
can help get
the old noodle going.

08:13.994 --> 08:16.562
Ah...

08:16.564 --> 08:18.030
His name's...

08:18.032 --> 08:19.665
Simon Tremblay.

08:19.667 --> 08:21.033
I should have known.

08:21.035 --> 08:22.067
Eh.

08:22.069 --> 08:23.252
Thanks for the free donuts.

08:23.254 --> 08:24.570
They're just donuts!

08:24.572 --> 08:26.739
Okay? They're like
two for a loonie-- <i>dollar.</i>

08:26.741 --> 08:27.923
What's happening?

08:27.925 --> 08:30.743
Oh, somebody moosed down
all the jellies.

08:30.745 --> 08:33.412
Have you been hanging
out with Turk Grimsby?

08:34.748 --> 08:36.432
So how serious
were you and Robin?

08:36.433 --> 08:39.268
Well, serious enough
to pop the question.

08:39.270 --> 08:40.385
Wow. Really?

08:40.388 --> 08:41.587
Yeah, sure.

08:41.589 --> 08:43.188
Got down on one goalie pad,

08:43.191 --> 08:44.640
I said, "Robin,

08:44.642 --> 08:47.643
could we keep dating but I get
to stick it to other babes?"

08:47.645 --> 08:48.978
Turned me down.

08:48.980 --> 08:50.896
I'm so sorry.

08:50.898 --> 08:51.897
Oh, that's okay.

08:51.899 --> 08:53.983
I really wanted to stick it
to Louise Marsh.

08:55.069 --> 08:57.203
Still, as the years pass,

08:57.205 --> 08:59.705
and you take stock of your life,

08:59.707 --> 09:02.941
part of me wishes I could've
kept sticking it to Robin, too.

09:04.127 --> 09:06.212
So are you the one
that Robin stalked?

09:06.214 --> 09:09.448
Oh, that story goes back
to the 1996 Grey Cup.

09:09.450 --> 09:11.634
What in God's name is that?

09:11.636 --> 09:13.185
Only Canada's Super Bowl.

09:13.187 --> 09:14.220
Didn't you
ever see

09:14.222 --> 09:15.671
<i>Underneath the Tunes</i>

09:15.673 --> 09:16.889
on MuchMusic?

09:16.891 --> 09:18.224
Again, I have to go with:

09:18.226 --> 09:20.810
what in God's name is that?

