All it needs
is a shirtless old man

12:48.388 --> 12:50.205
in black and white
for no reason.

12:53.427 --> 12:55.659
♪ I'll never move on,
it'll always be you ♪

12:55.759 --> 12:57.525
♪ Every guy that I'm with,
I'll be thinking of you ♪

12:57.527 --> 13:01.713
♪ If I get married,
he'll always be second to you ♪

13:01.715 --> 13:03.164
That's got to feel good.

13:03.166 --> 13:07.068
♪ I'll always
be waiting for you ♪

13:07.070 --> 13:09.754
♪ P.S. I love you.

13:10.506 --> 13:14.324
In 1996, we booked the halftime
show for the Grey Cup.

13:14.326 --> 13:15.693
Huge gig.

13:15.695 --> 13:17.861
We're talking Ivor Wynne Stadium
in Hamilton,

13:17.863 --> 13:20.781
<i>just outside of Guelph.</i>

13:20.783 --> 13:23.684
It doesn't get any bigger
than that.

13:23.686 --> 13:25.552
Hello, Canada.

13:25.554 --> 13:27.988
I'm Robin Sparkles.

13:27.990 --> 13:29.640
Oh.

13:32.578 --> 13:34.128
Actually...

13:34.130 --> 13:37.097
I was Robin Sparkles.

13:37.099 --> 13:38.699
The whole stadium went silent.

13:38.701 --> 13:41.819
Right then, I knew something
terrible was gonna happen.

13:41.821 --> 13:44.204
My stomach started churning.

13:44.206 --> 13:47.091
But Robin Sparkles is dead.

13:47.093 --> 13:50.477
All I could hear was Paul
Shaffer's stomach growling.

13:50.479 --> 13:53.180
Stress goes to my stomach--
sue me.

13:53.182 --> 13:55.215
It was kind of disgusting.

13:55.217 --> 13:56.450
I'm sorry, Jason Priestley,

13:56.452 --> 13:58.919
I didn't realize
you were the Queen of England.

13:59.473 --> 14:02.357
My new name is...

14:02.939 --> 14:05.106
Robin Daggers!

14:05.108 --> 14:06.591
Two, three, four!

14:06.593 --> 14:09.277
♪ You, you're beautiful

14:09.279 --> 14:10.661
<i>That day is now</i>

14:10.663 --> 14:15.283
known in music history
as the day grunge was born.

14:15.285 --> 14:16.568
In 1996, in Canada?

14:16.570 --> 14:18.036
That seems right, Trebek.

14:18.038 --> 14:20.138
Give him a break,
he's not a music guy.

14:20.140 --> 14:22.257
That day is now known
in music history

14:22.259 --> 14:24.859
as the day that grunge was born.

14:24.861 --> 14:26.310
Well, that's a bummer.

14:27.630 --> 14:28.863
It was tragic.

14:28.865 --> 14:30.164
I mean, to this day,

14:30.166 --> 14:32.450
you ask any Canadian
where they were

14:32.452 --> 14:35.520
when Robin Sparkles lost it,
not only can they tell you

14:35.522 --> 14:39.507
which Tim Hortons they were in,
but what donut they were eating.

14:39.509 --> 14:42.277
Me? Wawa, Ontario.

14:42.279 --> 14:43.695
Blueberry fritter.

14:43.697 --> 14:45.613
Halifax, Nova Scotia.

14:45.615 --> 14:47.315
Walnut crunch.

14:47.317 --> 14:48.833
Victoriaville, Quebec.

14:48.835 --> 14:50.451
Sour cream plain.

14:50.453 --> 14:52.754
Sudbury, Ontario.

14:52.756 --> 14:54.072
Honey dip.

14:54.074 --> 14:55.940
Red Deer, Alberta.

14:55.942 --> 14:57.842
Chocolate glaze.

14:57.844 --> 15:00.144
Squamish, British Columbia.

15:00.146 --> 15:02.664
Crammed a Timbit
into a strawberry vanilla

15:02.666 --> 15:04.699
and invented The Priestley.

15:04.701 --> 15:07.251
Should've been
the best day of my life.

15:07.253 --> 15:10.354
<i>It was horrifying</i>
<i>on so many levels.</i>

15:11.408 --> 15:13.825
Actually, you know what?

15:13.827 --> 15:15.843
I'm sorry, I can't...

15:15.845 --> 15:18.029
I just can't talk about this.

15:18.031 --> 15:20.581
I'm out of here, okay?
I'm out of here.

15:20.583 --> 15:21.966
Here, excuse me.

15:21.968 --> 15:22.934
I'm sorry, will you take...

15:22.936 --> 15:24.252
No, no, don't move, I'm out...

15:24.254 --> 15:25.753
Sorry, sorry.

15:25.755 --> 15:27.588
Speculation began immediately.

15:27.590 --> 15:29.290
<i>Who was Robin Sparkles</i>
<i>singing about</i>

15:29.292 --> 15:31.709
<i>with those angry,</i>
<i>obsessive lyrics?</i>

15:31.711 --> 15:33.361
<i>Many names were suggested.</i>

15:33.363 --> 15:34.746
It wasn't me.

15:34.748 --> 15:35.680
It wasn't me.

15:35.682 --> 15:36.848
Wasn't me.

15:36.850 --> 15:37.882
It wasn't me.

15:37.884 --> 15:38.866
It wasn't me.

15:38.868 --> 15:40.584
It wasn't me.

15:40.586 --> 15:43.671
Why does everyone always think

15:43.673 --> 15:45.239
it's me?

15:45.241 --> 15:47.191
I wish it was me.

15:47.193 --> 15:49.060
<i>But one name comes up</i>
<i>more than any other.</i>

15:49.062 --> 15:52.363
Alan Thicke.

15:52.365 --> 15:53.965
How can I help you?

15:53.967 --> 15:55.450
Donut?

15:56.568 --> 15:57.602
Whoa!

16:05.484 --> 16:08.302
Whoa. What
happened to you?

16:08.304 --> 16:12.556
We watched <i>Robin Sparkles:</i>
<i>Underneath the Tunes</i> today.

16:12.558 --> 16:14.191
Wait, what?

16:14.193 --> 16:16.794
You guys get
MuchMusic down here?

16:17.496 --> 16:20.748
And that video lead me to...

16:20.750 --> 16:23.701
I am engaged
to Robin Scherbatsky,

16:23.703 --> 16:26.754
and I know that she wrote
"P.S. I Love You" for you.

16:26.756 --> 16:29.307
Now-now, why is she
so obsessed with you?

16:29.309 --> 16:31.875
What? That song's
not about me.

16:31.877 --> 16:33.377
Then who is it "aboot"-- about.

16:33.379 --> 16:34.645
Damn it.

16:34.647 --> 16:36.046
I don't know.

16:36.048 --> 16:37.598
I always thought
it was Coulier.

16:37.600 --> 16:39.433
It wasn't me.

16:39.435 --> 16:41.051
Stop asking.

16:41.053 --> 16:43.220
Geez, cut it out.

16:43.222 --> 16:46.741
<i>I always liked that joke.</i>

16:46.743 --> 16:49.327
Alan Thicke kicked your ass.

16:50.279 --> 16:51.696
He lied, didn't he?

16:51.698 --> 16:53.831
It was Alan Thicke!

16:53.833 --> 16:55.032
Wow.

16:55.034 --> 16:56.083
It sounds like you've become

16:56.085 --> 16:58.035
a bit obsessed, huh, Barney?

16:58.037 --> 16:59.537
I am not obsessed.

16:59.539 --> 17:01.872
All I did was break
into your apartment

17:01.874 --> 17:03.174
and read your teenage journals,

17:03.176 --> 17:06.926
and fly to Vancouver to
interrogate your ex-boyfriends,

17:06.929 --> 17:11.214
and fight beloved
Canadian actor Alan Thicke

17:11.217 --> 17:13.017
to a draw.

17:13.019 --> 17:15.386
Ow, ow, ow,
ow, ow, ow!

17:15.387 --> 17:16.887
So,

17:16.888 --> 17:18.189
ready to admit it?

17:19.642 --> 17:22.359
Anyone can get obsessed.

17:22.362 --> 17:23.810
Thank you.

17:23.813 --> 17:26.262
And now, I am ready to tell you

17:26.265 --> 17:28.449
who "P.S. I Love You" is about.

17:28.451 --> 17:30.100
Who?

17:30.102 --> 17:31.786
"P.S."

17:32.571 --> 17:33.821
Paul Shaffer.

17:33.823 --> 17:36.457
Paul Shaffer?

17:36.459 --> 17:39.710
I know, so stereotypical.

17:39.712 --> 17:42.546
<i>Every young Canadian girl</i>
<i>fantasizes</i>

17:42.548 --> 17:44.715
<i>about being with Paul Shaffer.</i>

17:46.501 --> 17:49.620
At the Grey Cup gig, Paul was
sitting in the front row.

17:49.622 --> 17:54.091
♪ I'll always be
waiting for you ♪

17:54.093 --> 17:55.926
No wonder his stomach
was growling.

17:55.928 --> 17:58.929
I feel bad that I scared Paul.

17:58.931 --> 18:01.665
He's amazing.

18:02.334 --> 18:04.318
But I have no regrets.

18:04.320 --> 18:06.237
I was done being Robin Sparkles.

18:06.239 --> 18:07.188
You're not
gonna go get

18:07.190 --> 18:09.807
beat up by Paul Shaffer now,
are you?

18:09.809 --> 18:11.325
I can't believe it.

18:11.327 --> 18:13.611
I'm a total Dahmer.

18:13.613 --> 18:15.746
Yeah, but you're my Dahmer,

18:15.748 --> 18:17.164
which makes you a Dobler.

18:17.166 --> 18:20.067
Just like Jeanette.

18:20.069 --> 18:21.285
No, Ted,

18:21.287 --> 18:24.622
what that woman did to run in
to you was bonkers.

18:24.624 --> 18:26.257
That's just not how you start
a healthy relationship.

18:26.259 --> 18:27.708
Tell him, Lil.

18:27.710 --> 18:29.510
I can't stand
it anymore.

18:29.512 --> 18:31.178
I've been living a lie.

18:31.180 --> 18:33.347
See?

18:33.349 --> 18:34.715
<i>I saw you at orientation</i>

18:34.717 --> 18:37.000
<i>and I needed an excuse</i>
<i>to meet you,</i>

18:37.002 --> 18:37.968
<i>so...</i>

18:37.970 --> 18:39.670
Ah!

18:39.672 --> 18:41.004
<i>I didn't know which room</i>
<i>you were in,</i>

18:41.006 --> 18:44.692
<i>so I had to create</i>
<i>a little destiny.</i>

18:57.156 --> 18:58.572
Okay.

19:02.494 --> 19:04.027
I'm sorry, I just

19:04.029 --> 19:07.047
couldn't stand the idea
of not meeting you.

19:08.100 --> 19:09.333
Could...

19:09.335 --> 19:12.202
not stand the idea

19:12.204 --> 19:13.971
of not meeting me.

19:18.427 --> 19:20.010
I'm sorry, Ted.

19:20.012 --> 19:21.228
You were right.

19:21.230 --> 19:23.347
Jeanette's a Dobler.

19:23.349 --> 19:24.732
So are you.

19:24.734 --> 19:27.050
Thanks, buddy.

19:27.052 --> 19:29.236
You know, if you
hadn't been reading

19:29.238 --> 19:30.604
the exact same book as me,

19:30.606 --> 19:32.189
we never would've met.

19:32.191 --> 19:33.657
I mean, that's destiny.

19:33.659 --> 19:35.776
Oh, look.

19:35.778 --> 19:37.945
You bought it in the
same bookstore I did.

19:37.947 --> 19:40.247
On the same day.

19:40.249 --> 19:44.034
Within ten minutes
of me buying mine.

19:44.036 --> 19:45.870
Ugh...

19:45.872 --> 19:47.455
Uh, this is embarrassing.

19:47.457 --> 19:48.539
I wasn't gonna tell you this,

19:48.541 --> 19:51.909
but I followed you
to that bookstore.

19:51.911 --> 19:55.629
I just couldn't stand
the idea of not meeting you.

19:55.631 --> 19:58.766
You followed me
to the bookstore from where?

19:58.768 --> 20:01.352
How long have you
been following me?

20:01.354 --> 20:03.854
Uh, this is embarrassing.

20:03.856 --> 20:06.774
Uh, remember when you were on
the cover of <i>New York Magazine?</i>

20:06.776 --> 20:09.643
That was like a year
and a half ago.

20:09.645 --> 20:12.029
Yeah.

20:12.031 --> 20:14.548
<i>Before a man meets</i>
<i>the woman he'll marry,</i>

20:14.550 --> 20:17.618
<i>he'll make one final,</i>
<i>horrible mistake.</i>

20:17.620 --> 20:20.087
<i>For me, that was Jeanette.</i>

